column5: Should have been out a few weeks ago but have been dealing with back problems and an infection. Hit my favorite early season laker spot and landed a few small ones and a few small burbot as well. Lost a bunch of lakers and burbies too (darn barbless regs!!!    ). Got to the lake and went to start the old Strikemaster annnnnd................................ the old pig took 2 whole yanks to get her started!!! We got good ice but need more snow. The trail in was pretty rough and I had some issues in a couple of places spinning the track out on gravel but there is some snow on the way. We have enough Ice now that a foot of snow would be most welcome. Anywho, here's some porn for y'all!!! Enjoy!!!!    Got a new tent for the old Trekker II (replaced the original with a Trekker DLX tent which is twice as thick)
Wow!  Gorgeous lakers...green with envy over here...pun intended...
that's just wrong   there should be a rule, no ice fishing posts till everyone can ice fish...lol   nice looking fish
Awesome dude, still at least 4-6 weeks away from first ice down here. 'Can't wait.
Nice laker. Catching fish through the ice already, definitely jealous.
Nice  I'm guessing 3 weeks till we can get out here....bring it on!
That's just not fair!  Sweet looking Laker.  The pic inside the hut of the flasher and heater is getting me excited!  At least another month for us down here in south Ont.  Rick
That is awesome. I can't wait until the ice is here.  Some nice fish you got there Dave.

Ha ha. This morning I said "I'm going to check OFC every day, and when someone starts posting pics of ice fishing I'm going to drive there to get some done"....... maybe a little far. That being said, sweet lakers. I'm jelous.
nice fish, it's good to see winter hardwater reports coming up again, you must be running low on daylight up there?
Hey Brian  Ya never know!  Many a year I have a had a feed of fresh Simcoe Perch ,before Turkey Day  Rick
